==English==
===Etymology===
From Greek [[ἑτεροουσιος]], from [[hetero-]] ‘same’ + [[ουσια]] ‘essence’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/hɛtərəʊ'u:zɪən/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|heteroousian}}
# having different [[essence]] or [[substance]], especially with reference to the first and second persons of the [[Trinity]]

